BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:zj200bG4LbHVbqs4mMboj
SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260326T160825Z
DTSTART:20260327T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Friday\, March 27\, 2026\, 11am - 4pm\n\nTrained volunteers wil
	l be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.\n\nLo
	cation Link:\n\nSouthwest Branch\n\nRoom Location: Meeting Room\n\nRegistr
	ation Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed Description: Thi
	s service is free and available to individuals only. The free service is n
	ot available for business tax returns. To receive tax help\, bring the fol
	lowing documents:\,\n\nRequired:\n\nPhoto identification\, Social Security
	 cards or Individual Taxpayer Identification Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyo
	ne listed on the tax return.\, Proof of income\, for example\, W2s and 109
	9s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Official documents on Social Security 
	Administration letterhead\, Medicare card \\(if Social Security number is 
	followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to provide information about health ca
	re coverage for each person on the return.\,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year&
	's tax return\, if available\, Bank account and routing numbers for direct
	 deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or computer print-outs of any of these d
	ocuments willbe accepted.\, Due to federal budget cuts the IRS is unable t
	o provide the Library with certain tax forms and instruction booklets.\, M
	ost IRS forms are available online at\n\nwww.irs.gov .\, You may make free
	 black-and-white prints of the forms from Library computers:\n\nwww.spl.or
	g/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nAARP .\n\nEvent Logistics: Appointment
	s are not required but recommended. Register\n\nhere. \, AARP Tax Help loc
	ations serve anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025.\, For eligibili
	ty details\, contact AARP at 888-227-7669.\,\n\nContact Us: If you have qu
	estions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accom
	modations: We can provide accommodations for people with disabilities at L
	ibrary events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the eve
	nt to request accommodations.\, All Library programs are free and open to 
	the public.\, The Southwest Branch is accessible by the 21\, 22\, and C Li
	ne buses.\, Free parking in our lot and free street parking is available.\
	, The second-floor meeting room is accessible by elevator\, or two flights
	 of stairs with railings. ADA-accessible restrooms are available on the se
	cond floor.\, Ask staff if you need assistive devices \\(such as magnifyin
	g glasses\\) during the event.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/de
	tails/free-tax-help/18162991/2026-03-27T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & E
	ducation
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/20
	26-03-27T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:La79OLCOJTlnnmC8UglXq
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260326T160825Z
DTSTART:20260327T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-03
	-27T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-03-27T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:akd6LXagUtLWvaSOOG5wA
SUMMARY:La Hora de Cuentos
DTSTAMP:20260326T160825Z
DTSTART:20260327T181500Z
DESCRIPTION:Friday\, March 27\, 2026\, 11:15am - 12:15pm\n\nDurante la hora
	 de cuentos\, los niños de 0 a 5 años y sus familias pueden disfrutar de h
	istorias\, canciones y divertidas actividades de aprendizaje.\n\nEvento en
	 español.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nGreenwood Branch\n\nRoom Location: Meeting 
	Room\n\nRegistration Required: No se requiere inscripción.\n\nDetailed Des
	cription: El aprendizaje temprano es una excelente manera para que los niñ
	os de 0 a 5 años y sus familias desarrollen habilidades de aprendizaje\, a
	lfabetización y lenguaje\, así como una comunidad con otras familias.\, Le
	emos cuentos\, cantamos canciones y tenemos actividades educativas atracti
	vas que ayudan a los niños y sus cuidadores a crecer juntos.\,\n\n--------
	-----------------------------------------\, At storytime\, kids ages 0-5 a
	nd their families can enjoy stories\, songs\, and fun learning activities.
	\, Early Learning is a great way for kids ages 0-5 and their families to d
	evelop learning\, literacy\, and language skills as well as community with
	 other families.\, We read stories\, sing songs\, and have engaging\, educ
	ational activities that help kids and their caregivers grow together.\,\n\
	nEvent Logistics: Este evento se llevará a cabo en español.\, No se requie
	re inscripción\, pero estos programas son muy populares y la capacidad de 
	la sala puede llenarse rápidamente.\, Las familias de todas las edades son
	 bienvenidas\, aunque este programa de aprendizaje temprano está diseñado 
	para niños de 0 a 5 años\, sus cuidadores y familias.\,\n\n---------------
	----------------------------------\, This event will take place in Spanish
	.\, Registration is not required but these programs are very popular and t
	he room capacity can fill up quickly.\, Families of all ages are welcome\,
	 though this early learning program is intended for youth aged 0-5\, their
	 caregivers and families.\,\n\nContact Us: Si tiene alguna pregunta sobre 
	este evento\,\n\npregúntenos\n\no llame al 206-386-4636.\,\n\n------------
	-------------------------------------\, If you have questions about this e
	vent\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: Podemos o
	frecer acomodamiento para personas con discapacidades en los eventos de la
	 biblioteca. Póngase encontacto con\n\nLEAP\n\nal menos siete días antes d
	el evento para solicitar acomodamiento.\, Todos los programas de la biblio
	teca son gratuitos y abiertos al público.\,\n\n---------------------------
	----------------------\, We can provide accommodations for people with dis
	abilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days 
	before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library programs are fre
	e and open to the public.\,\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/detai
	ls/la-hora-de-cuentos/17650265/2026-03-27T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/la-hora-de-cuentos/176502
	65/2026-03-27T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
